Extract polygons from dense cell segmentation

Shila Ghazanfar

15/06/2020

Load functions

source("../scripts/segmentation_functions.R")

Load some example data

data = readRDS("../data/dense_segmentation_example.Rds")

This is a dense cell segmentation per pixel, which also contains some sparse segments that do not correspond to real cells.

Extract polygons

This function will extract the smallest set of vertices that can accurately reflect the polygon structure of the segmentation. This method only works for solid segments (no doughnuts!).

boundary_polygons = extractPolygonsFromSegmentation(
    data,
    modes = c("boundaryPolygons"),
    cellFilterFactor = 5,
    minPixels = 50,
    cellPrefix = "cell_",
    cellSuffix = "",
    plot = TRUE,
    verbose = FALSE
)
## Loading required package: reshape
## Loading required package: ggplot2
## Loading required package: patchwork
colnames(boundary_polygons) <- c("x","y","cell","uniqueID")

dim(boundary_polygons)
## [1] 28690     4
head(boundary_polygons)
##   x  y cell uniqueID
## 1 8 76    2   cell_2
## 7 8 77    2   cell_2
## 6 7 77    2   cell_2
## 5 6 77    2   cell_2
## 4 5 77    2   cell_2
## 3 4 77    2   cell_2
boundary_polygons <- pruneStraightLines(boundary_polygons, group = "uniqueID")

dim(boundary_polygons)
## [1] 14840     4
head(boundary_polygons)
##     x  y cell uniqueID
## 1   8 76    2   cell_2
## 7   8 77    2   cell_2
## 2   3 77    2   cell_2
## 12  2 78    2   cell_2
## 11  1 78    2   cell_2
## 290 1 97    2   cell_2
g1 = ggplot(boundary_polygons, aes(x = x, y = y, group = uniqueID)) + 
    geom_polygon(aes(fill = uniqueID), alpha = 0.5, colour = "black", size = 0.3) + 
    theme_classic() + 
    theme(legend.position = "none") +
    ggtitle("Extracted polygons using dense segmentation") +
    coord_fixed() +
    NULL
g1

Faster (but less accurate) approach using convex hull

boundary_polygons_chull = extractPolygonsFromSegmentation(
    data,
    modes = c("chull"),
    cellFilterFactor = 5,
    minPixels = 50,
    cellPrefix = "cell_",
    cellSuffix = "",
    plot = TRUE,
    verbose = FALSE
)
# much faster but not as clean
colnames(boundary_polygons_chull) <- c("x","y","z", "value", "cell","uniqueID")

dim(boundary_polygons_chull)
## [1] 5268    6

g2 = ggplot(boundary_polygons_chull, aes(x = x, y = y, group = uniqueID)) + 
    geom_polygon(aes(fill = uniqueID), alpha = 0.5, colour = "black", size = 0.3) + 
    theme_classic() + 
    theme(legend.position = "none") +
    ggtitle("Extracted polygons using convex hull") +
    coord_fixed() +
    NULL
